1
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:25,240
Yufan, have you finished reading those student files?

2
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:26,360
I've finished.

3
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:28,800
Sigh, these kids.

4
00:00:29,720 --> 00:00:32,400
They're afraid the school will communicate with their parents,

5
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:35,200
so they are being secretive about this loan issue.

6
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:36,980
Isn't this just nonsense?

7
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:39,640
If they could solve this problem themselves,

8
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:41,320
why would we need to intervene?

9
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:42,920
But these students,

10
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:44,200
I don't know them either.

11
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:45,520
But rumor has it

12
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:47,360
that this lending started last year.

13
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:47,920
Ah.

14
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:50,920
You were the president of the student union at that time.

15
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:53,520
Don't you have any impression of these people?

16
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:55,640
When you were in the student union,

17
00:00:55,640 --> 00:00:57,640
did you hear any rumors about loans?

18
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:03,840
Do you know how high the interest rate of this company's loan is?

19
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:05,840
We can't just leave our student union members

20
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:06,970
in the lurch, can we?

21
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,280
You are pushing him into the abyss.

22
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:12,340
Does he have the ability to pay back such high interest?

23
00:01:12,960 --> 00:01:15,280
You're right. Then what should we do?

24
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,840
I will lend him my own money.

25
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,200
Don't worry.

26
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,840
If that's the case,

27
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:31,370
Hey, can those loan documents still be found?

28
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:33,880
Probably.

29
00:01:34,080 --> 00:01:35,740
The borrower still has a copy.

30
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:36,920
Okay.

31
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:38,160
However,

32
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:40,039
just with these documents,

33
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,280
I still can't confirm

34
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:44,080
whether Wang Yu issued the loan.

35
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:46,360
I'll confirm it.

36
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:53,479
The teacher has found the loan company's info.

37
00:01:53,479 --> 00:01:56,210
I'm worried they'll get my data from the company.

38
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:58,280
I've missed several payments.

39
00:01:58,280 --> 00:01:59,840
The company threatened me before

40
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,000
that if I miss another payment,

41
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,280
they'll contact my family.

42
00:02:02,280 --> 00:02:04,800
I'm worried they won't keep my info confidential.

43
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:05,320
How about this.

44
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:06,720
I'll find another platform for you.

45
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:09,000
You can borrow from there to tide yourself over.

46
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:09,840
Thank you.

47
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:11,680
If my mom finds out, she'll kill me.

48
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:12,600
Thank you.

49
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,079
This is the last student.

50
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:23,260
Are there any other companies that can lend to them?

51
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:25,200
Let's take some of our commission

52
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:26,480
and lend it to her.

53
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:28,079
That's the only way.

54
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,840
That's not just a little profit.

55
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:31,640
It means we did all this for nothing.

56
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:33,800
We could also raise the interest rate.

57
00:02:34,079 --> 00:02:35,880
Then we'd make another killing.

58
00:02:36,079 --> 00:02:37,810
But we have to collect it first.

59
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:41,880
Don't worry. Once we get back to the Student Union,

60
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,800
I have countless ways

61
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,120
to make her pay.

62
00:02:49,079 --> 00:02:51,800
This is the loan contract Wang Yu brought out last year.

63
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:54,000
I think I've heard of this loan company.

64
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Uncle He, can you look into it?

65
00:02:56,079 --> 00:02:59,360
An investigation can only reveal the company's personnel and assets.

66
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,400
Getting evidence

67
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:02,200
that the Student Union leaked student data

68
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:03,600
is highly unlikely.

69
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:06,820
Can we pretend to be from the loan company

70
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:08,720
and ask Wang Yu for the student data?

71
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:09,920
Mhm.

72
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,160
They have designated contacts.

73
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:13,160
Asking for data right now would be too obvious.

74
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:15,400
It's fine if it's someone we haven't worked with before.

75
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:17,120
Then we'll pretend to be a new loan company

76
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:18,160
and contact them.

77
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,040
Why?

78
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:22,440
Xihai University's

79
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:24,560
student loans

80
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:27,890
were unexpectedly reported on a live broadcast.

81
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:34,120
Wang Yu definitely doesn't dare to contact the previous companies now.

82
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:36,000
Then they will be very short on money

83
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,600
and definitely need a new company to take over.

84
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:40,480
Yeah, that's highly possible.

85
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:44,040
This is the best solution for now.

86
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,440
I'll go contact someone.

87
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:48,840
Sorry for the trouble, Uncle He.

88
00:03:51,079 --> 00:03:51,740
President.

89
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,000
A new loan company contacted us.

90
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,160
Are they reliable?

91
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:56,960
I asked around.

92
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:58,840
I heard they are quite reliable.

93
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,640
What are their requirements?

94
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:03,840
They want to verify the students' information with you in person.

95
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:04,960
We are miles apart.

96
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,460
How can I give it to him?

97
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:07,480
They will come over.

98
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:10,480
They said the manager happens to be in town these days.

99
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:12,360
What a coincidence. OPE TO THE E.

100
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:12,920
Ah.

101
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:16,100
It's much more reliable than lending out our own money.

102
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:17,740
President.

103
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:19,399
Even if we wanted to lend it out ourselves,

104
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:20,720
with so many students in debt,

105
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,380
how could we ever cover it all?

106
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,280
Did you agree on where to meet?

107
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:28,560
Not yet.

108
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:41,159
Didn't An Yufan arrange to meet him today?

109
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:46,050
Why is there no movement at all?

110
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:10,800
I didn't expect him to meet here.

111
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,480
Wouldn't it be better to just record it?

112
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,040
Why do we have to livestream it?

113
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,120
I'm not sure.

114
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:17,840
But Zixi wanted to livestream it.

115
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:19,300
She must have her reasons.

116
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:20,520
By the way,

117
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:23,120
did you communicate clearly with the teacher?

118
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:24,640
We did.

119
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:35,280
The internet isn't working here.

120
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:37,640
The IP is occupied, and the livestream port is blocked.

121
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:39,370
Did they set this up in advance?

122
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,000
Are you done?

123
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,800
It's almost time.

124
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,480
Hello, Mr. He.

125
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:07,380
Sorry to keep you waiting.

126
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:09,480
Are you the student council president?

127
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:12,680
The president has other matters to attend to, so I will be liaising with you.

128
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:14,280
Did you bring the information on the students taking out loans?

129
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:15,040
Take a look.

130
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,520
I was wondering

131
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,160
who was following me.

132
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:17,320
What a coincidence. Why are you here too?

133
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:18,650
What are you doing here?

134
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,250
I should be asking you that.

135
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,280
I was just curious about what happened.

136
00:07:22,280 --> 00:07:24,810
If there's nothing else, I'll be leaving now.

137
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,360
It's not good to take someone else's things.

138
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,640
Let me go.

139
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:34,880
Let go!

140
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:39,440
You set up those student loans, didn't you?

141
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,600
You meddle too much.

142
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,120
You know their parents

143
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:46,200
worked so hard to pay for their education,

144
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,840
only for them to return with a mountain of debt.

145
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:50,040
Do you know how devastated they will be?

146
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:52,280
They deserve it.

147
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:59,200
You took huge profit cuts from their loans

148
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,960
and forced them to take out new loans to pay off old ones.

149
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:03,520
How can you even say that?

150
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,880
I earned it.

151
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:08,400
I work for my commissions.

152
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:11,240
What about the students who didn't want a loan in the first place?

153
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,240
They didn't ask for your loans.

154
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,680
That's because I'm good at my job.

155
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:19,040
You're actually proud of being shameless.

156
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,500
Are you complimenting me?

157
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,040
Thanks.

158
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:24,360
Anything else you want to say?

159
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,360
But time is running out.

160
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,040
Do you know that your files

161
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,040
have already been found by An Yufan?

162
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:32,200
You'd better turn yourself in right now.

163
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,280
You mean

164
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:35,010
the ones Huiying brought over?

165
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:36,520
Mine aren't in there.

166
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,799
Mine are all here.

167
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:44,140
Why? Are you unwilling to give up?

168
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,930
Do you still want to guard this pile of documents?

169
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:50,240
Then don't blame me

170
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,520
for being impolite.

171
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,600
An Yufan.

172
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,930
Thank you for your confession.

173
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,480
What you just said

174
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:07,140
has been broadcast live by me.

175
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,800
Wang Yu, you have failed the school's trust in you.

176
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,160
Take him away.

177
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:29,100
Why didn't you wait for me?

178
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:31,240
I saw he hadn't taken the bait,

179
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,920
so I rushed in anxiously.

180
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,120
Thank you.

181
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:52,400
Deputy Actor Director: Xi Chongjing.

182
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,320
Props Assistant: Li Kunxiao.

183
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,240
Field Vehicle: Yi Mingle,

184
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:58,200
Yi Tong.
